\section{Conclusions}
We present a measurement of the forward-backward asymmetry in the production of $b\bar{b}$ pairs in proton-antiproton collisions at $\sqrt{s} = 1.96$ TeV using a sample from 6.9 fb$^{-1}$ of integrated luminosity collected by the CDF II detector. The measured value of the integrated asymmetry is $A_\mathrm{FB}(b\bar{b}) = (1.2 \pm 0.7)$\%. In addition, the dependence of the asymmetry $A_\mathrm{FB}$ on $b\bar{b}$-pair invariant mass, {\ensuremath{m_{{\ensuremath{b\bar{b}}\xspace}}}\xspace}{}, is measured. A tendency to an increase of {\ensuremath{A_\text{FB}({\ensuremath{b\bar{b}}\xspace})}\xspace} with {\ensuremath{m_{{\ensuremath{b\bar{b}}\xspace}}}\xspace}{} invariant mass is observed. The experimental value of {\ensuremath{A_\text{FB}({\ensuremath{b\bar{b}}\xspace})}\xspace} around the $Z$ boson mass follows the theoretical expectation that predicts a local increase due to the contribution of electroweak processes~\cite{Murphy}. This results is consistent with SM expectations and extends previous findings \cite{afbbb} to {\ensuremath{m_{{\ensuremath{b\bar{b}}\xspace}}}\xspace}{} values down to {\SI[per-mode=symbol]{{40}}{\giga\eV\per\clight\squared}\xspace}.

